I must admit, I was a bit skeptical at first but once I fired up Sonic2 I was actually impressed. With this emulator Sonic looks better on my Xperia Play than on my PSP 1000.    I tested out lots of different Genesis game roms I own and while most of the other emulators just look about the same as the PSP, this emulator makes each look like I'm running them in Kega Fusion for X86.   I tested out the one Master system rom I own (Phantasy Star) and again everything worked perfect.   One thing that surprised me on the negative side was the lack of GameGear support. Most Master System emulators also run GameGear games so I was surprised that my copy of the Lion King would not play.  Of course GameGear is not in the App description so I shouldn't really complain but let me just put my two cents in and ask ever so kindly if it is at all possible for the future.   The Emulator is totally worth the money without this, I'm just asking.  Lastly, it would also be nice to see 32x support. Sure there are only three decent games for that system but those three good games were nice. If not full 32x support, then a way to play the 32x versions of Mortal Kombat 2 and Virtua Fighter.
